President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Florida due to the effects of Hurricane Nicole. This declaration allows federal funding to be provided to affected individuals and businesses in Brevard, Flagler, Lake, Putnam, St. Johns, and Volusia Counties. Assistance may include grants for temporary housing, home repairs, and low-cost loans for uninsured property losses. Federal funding is also available for state and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, to cover the costs of emergency work and facility repairs. Additionally, funding is available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Thomas J. McCool has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance through the DisasterAssistance.gov website, by calling 800-621-FEMA (3362), or by using the FEMA App. Further information can be obtained by contacting the FEMA News Desk.